40:32.792 --> 40:34.417
How well do you know Tom?

40:34.417 --> 40:35.750
I knew his brother better.

40:35.750 --> 40:37.709
Do you consider him a friend?

40:37.709 --> 40:38.250
No.

40:38.250 --> 40:40.875
Tom became unreliable.

40:40.875 --> 40:43.500
You're not unreliable,
are you, Mr. Donovan?

40:43.500 --> 40:46.166
I mean, when someone
brings you into their problem,

40:46.166 --> 40:47.792
you're discreet.

40:47.792 --> 40:48.583
What's he got on you?

40:52.667 --> 40:54.542
I first met my husband Roger

40:54.542 --> 40:56.125
when I was
a script girl at Pacific.

40:56.125 --> 40:59.959
He was 56.
I was 29.

40:59.959 --> 41:02.250
The film was
The Absolute End.

41:02.250 --> 41:04.291
He proposed to me

41:04.291 --> 41:06.500
the night he won the Oscar.

41:08.166 --> 41:10.417
What happened?

41:10.417 --> 41:12.959
Our daughter, Ainsley, was born.

41:12.959 --> 41:14.458
Roger bought a house
on Point Dume.

41:14.458 --> 41:19.125
Which I hated.
The constant driving.

41:19.125 --> 41:20.792
Ainsley and George
liked to play

41:20.792 --> 41:23.375
at the Madisons' when he
wasn't with his mother.

41:23.375 --> 41:27.000
And the Madisons lived nearby.

41:27.000 --> 41:30.125
We drank, she and I.

41:30.125 --> 41:32.333
Too much.

41:32.333 --> 41:34.750
It was four-thirty.

41:34.750 --> 41:37.125
I remember because I was
due in town at six-thirty,

41:37.125 --> 41:40.000
and I was running late.

41:40.000 --> 41:43.000
December 16th.

41:43.000 --> 41:44.792
The sun was going down.

41:46.166 --> 41:48.917
Kids were in
the back of the car.

41:48.917 --> 41:52.208
I turned onto the PCH.

41:54.083 --> 41:56.000
I was drunk.

41:56.000 --> 41:59.709
Very drunk.

41:59.709 --> 42:01.709
The kids were...

42:01.709 --> 42:02.625
in the back seat.

42:10.458 --> 42:14.291
Um, Tom belonged
to Roger at that time,

42:14.291 --> 42:16.458
and he came to the hospital.

42:16.458 --> 42:18.500
I was handcuffed to the bed.

42:18.500 --> 42:23.375
And Tom did what he does.
He...

42:23.375 --> 42:26.709
he made it disappear.

42:26.709 --> 42:28.583
And Ainsley's death

42:28.583 --> 42:34.125
became a tragedy
instead of a crime.

42:34.125 --> 42:36.208
♪ somber ambient music ♪

42:36.208 --> 42:37.709
♪♪♪

42:37.709 --> 42:40.542
That must have been
hard for you.

42:40.542 --> 42:45.417
♪♪♪

42:45.417 --> 42:47.750
I suspected
that Tom kept things.

42:47.750 --> 42:49.291
Obviously, he did.

42:54.041 --> 42:54.834
I'll take care of it.

42:56.083 --> 42:58.917
Will you, Ray?

43:00.375 --> 43:02.583
